 you there.<br>
<br>
And the non-aggro spiders and fire beetles and will o wisps who wander all the way to the newbie log. And you know why? Cause they turned back on Project M! So bored PKers can come and skin-walk the bears and they can really track you down and follow you, and camp your 3rd level self's corpse or bind point. And you can't just train them to the guards, 'cause they'll just stop out of aggro range. Becasue they are players... Just like you and me....<br>
<br>
*shudders*<br>
<br>
As a note, bears can be out run. You just have to make sure you aren't too injured (I usually run at two bubbles of life with the wizzie), are not encumbered, and you learn how to glide step (has a number of different names, like strafeing). To accomplish this turn on auto-run, then hold down the Ctrl key and your left or right arrow. This will make you move forward at an angle, and you will move faster than you do when running. Verant's never quite fixed that bug... I know they are aware of it, they might even call it an exploit. But running away from bears isn't exactly a game ruining exploit. <p><center><a href="http://www.violentharvest.com"><img src="http://home.columbus.rr.com/harvest/khas_sig.jpg"></a><br>
